00:16:57,120 --> 00:16:59,440
Yes, our client is sensitive to rumors.

274
00:16:59,440 --> 00:17:00,790
Is that okay with you?

275
00:17:00,790 --> 00:17:02,090
I have no problem with that.

276
00:17:02,090 --> 00:17:08,840
But is running the golf course the reason or for investment?

277
00:17:08,840 --> 00:17:11,800
The client is a fund, but it's not to resell it.

278
00:17:11,800 --> 00:17:13,470
They will manage it directly.

279
00:17:13,470 --> 00:17:17,640
So the current CEO needs to be replaced.

280
00:17:17,640 --> 00:17:19,680
Is replacing only the CEO enough?

281
00:17:19,680 --> 00:17:24,250
Yes. The employees can stay as long as there aren't any issues.

282
00:17:24,250 --> 00:17:27,750
Please don't take all the good employees with you.

283
00:17:27,750 --> 00:17:29,430
All right.

284
00:17:29,430 --> 00:17:31,630
What's the value you have in mind?

285
00:17:31,630 --> 00:17:34,880
Wouldn't 80 billion won be reasonable?

286
00:17:35,500 --> 00:17:37,430
That's too low.

287
00:17:37,430 --> 00:17:40,570
You're open to going higher, right?

288
00:17:40,570 --> 00:17:41,990
Mr. Yun,

289
00:17:41,990 --> 00:17:45,290
everyone knows Sanin is desperate for cash right now.

290
00:17:45,290 --> 00:17:50,640
Also, the golf industry isn't that attractive these days.

291
00:17:50,640 --> 00:17:54,220
We already have a plan to raise the funds.

292
00:17:54,220 --> 00:17:57,730
So we don't really have to sell the golf course.

293
00:17:57,730 --> 00:17:59,140
Eleven trillion won?

294
00:17:59,140 --> 00:18:01,450
There's not much of that left now.

295
00:18:01,450 --> 00:18:03,870
The project is in its final stages too.

296
00:18:03,870 --> 00:18:05,750
Thank you.

297
00:18:06,420 --> 00:18:10,490
I thought you'd heard about Mr. Yun.

298
00:18:14,080 --> 00:18:18,170
Then should I contact you after reviewing it?

299
00:18:18,170 --> 00:18:20,750
Yes. Let's do that.

300
00:18:26,660 --> 00:18:28,210
Thank you for coming today.

301
00:18:28,210 --> 00:18:29,750
Thank you.

302
00:18:30,470 --> 00:18:32,250
- I'll give you a call. 
 - Yes, I'll call you.

303
00:18:32,250 --> 00:18:33,990
I'll call you.

304
00:18:41,650 --> 00:18:43,570
I feel like I'm losing for some reason.

305
00:18:43,570 --> 00:18:45,280
I'm the one who's buying.

306
00:18:45,280 --> 00:18:47,350
It always feels like that, talking to Mr. Yun.

307
00:18:47,350 --> 00:18:49,190
He's not called White Snake for no reason.

308
00:18:49,190 --> 00:18:51,990
But isn't 80 billion won a bit too low?

309
00:18:51,990 --> 00:18:55,270
Hey, that's a pretty high offer.

310
00:18:55,270 --> 00:18:56,830
Not that you don't have the ammunition?

311
00:18:56,830 --> 00:18:58,370
We've got more than enough ammunition!

312
00:18:58,370 --> 00:19:00,360
Do you want me to just shoot you?

313
00:19:00,360 --> 00:19:02,520
That's good.

314
00:19:02,520 --> 00:19:05,530
But who did you say was the client again?

315
00:19:05,530 --> 00:19:07,690
No-name basis!

316
00:19:07,690 --> 00:19:09,770
Oh, right, right. You said that.

317
00:19:09,770 --> 00:19:11,610
Okay.

318
00:19:12,470 --> 00:19:14,690
What's a no-name basis?

319
00:19:14,690 --> 00:19:16,350
It's exactly as it sounds.

320
00:19:16,350 --> 00:19:20,530
It's called a no-name basis when the buyer isn't disclosed.

321
00:19:20,530 --> 00:19:22,920
Is that legal?

322
00:19:22,920 --> 00:19:24,520
It happens all the time.

323
00:19:24,520 --> 00:19:26,990
When the buyer is a big company

324
00:19:26,990 --> 00:19:30,570
or if the special info regarding the specific company is leaked,

325
00:19:30,570 --> 00:19:34,040
the other side could ask for a higher price.

326
00:19:34,590 --> 00:19:36,610
So they keep their identity a secret to the end?

327
00:19:36,610 --> 00:19:37,820
No.

328
00:19:37,820 --> 00:19:41,960
The buyer should show themselves when we agree to sell.

329
00:19:54,380 --> 00:19:57,630
Mr. Yun, I heard you went to Mt. Bukhan.

330
00:19:57,630 --> 00:19:59,390
Yes.

331
00:19:59,390 --> 00:20:01,620
I guess I'll be seeing you often.

332
00:20:09,750 --> 00:20:12,370
 The doors are closing. 

333
00:20:19,970 --> 00:20:24,200
You'll have a lot of questions once you become an executive.

334
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:28,640
Feel free to ask me any time if there's anything you don't know.

335
00:20:28,640 --> 00:20:30,880
Thank you for saying that.

336
00:20:31,450 --> 00:20:34,830
Or we can grab dinner with Mr. Lee sometime.

337
00:20:36,760 --> 00:20:38,270
Okay.

338
00:20:40,930 --> 00:20:42,330
Let's go.

339
00:20:42,330 --> 00:20:45,400
Attorney Oh hasn't come in yet.

340
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:47,420
He's probably already there.

341
00:20:47,420 --> 00:20:49,540
A-At the golf course?

342
00:20:49,540 --> 00:20:52,560
Chungbuk is Attorney Oh's hometown.

343
00:20:58,890 --> 00:20:59,530
  ­ 

344
00:20:59,530 --> 00:21:02,470
 - Enjoy your meal. 
 - Thank you. 

345
00:21:05,410 --> 00:21:07,450
Sun Young is perfect.

346
00:21:07,450 --> 00:21:12,810
I know, right? He's handsome, has a good personality, and he's a prosecutor!

347
00:21:12,810 --> 00:21:14,500
I'm not a prosecutor.

348
00:21:14,500 --> 00:21:16,520
You quit your job as one.

349
00:21:16,520 --> 00:21:18,460
Now, he's an attorney for Sanin.

350
00:21:18,460 --> 00:21:19,800
Exactly.

351
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:21,470
I heard that pays him more.

352
00:21:21,470 --> 00:21:23,200
Wow, you make a lot of money, too?

353
00:21:23,200 --> 00:21:25,410
Why aren't you getting married, then?

354
00:21:25,410 --> 00:21:27,760
Right? But it's not that I'm not marrying.

355
00:21:27,760 --> 00:21:29,740
He's got high standards, just like his dad.

356
00:21:29,740 --> 00:21:33,590
Aigoo, I guess your mom won't be getting our food money*. 
  (*referring to money gifted in return for eating at the wedding) 

357
00:21:33,590 --> 00:21:35,650
Sun Young, you need to meet a good woman.

358
00:21:35,650 --> 00:21:38,350
Don't be like your dad and just date anyone, okay?

359
00:21:38,350 --> 00:21:39,690
Give me a freaking break.

360
00:21:39,690 --> 00:21:42,240
It's a good thing I had low standards.

361
00:21:42,240 --> 00:21:45,140
If I didn't, my Sun Yeong wouldn't even be in the world!

362
00:21:45,140 --> 00:21:48,530
Aigoo, then I'm grateful to my mom, too.

363
00:21:48,530 --> 00:21:50,140
Not your dad?

364
00:21:50,140 --> 00:21:52,100
I take after my dad.

365
00:21:52,100 --> 00:21:53,190
Look at me.

366
00:21:53,190 --> 00:21:56,280
Oh, you're right, you're right!

367
00:21:59,150 --> 00:22:00,940
Oh Sun Young!

368
00:22:05,320 --> 00:22:06,750
Bon Ju! Bon Ju!

369
00:22:06,750 --> 00:22:08,060
Hey, i-it's been a while!

370
00:22:08,060 --> 00:22:10,140
It's been a while. I heard you became a prosecutor.

371
00:22:10,140 --> 00:22:11,340
- Yes. 
 - He quit.

372
00:22:11,340 --> 00:22:13,460
He's a Sanin attorney now.

373
00:22:13,460 --> 00:22:15,070
Yes, well, thank you.

374
00:22:15,070 --> 00:22:17,540
Oh, yes, sit here, sit, sit.

375
00:22:18,760 --> 00:22:20,870
Yes, being a prosecutor doesn't fit you.

376
00:22:20,870 --> 00:22:22,450
Right?

377
00:22:23,240 --> 00:22:25,200
So how are you doing?

378
00:22:25,200 --> 00:22:27,000
Me? I'm doing all right.

379
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:28,680
I'm working at a golf course.

380
00:22:28,680 --> 00:22:30,940
Really? Hey, that's great—

381
00:22:30,940 --> 00:22:32,670
Oh Sun Young!

382
00:22:32,670 --> 00:22:35,830
Oh Class President, it's been so long!

383
00:22:35,830 --> 00:22:38,590
Hey! Hey, it's been so long!

384
00:22:38,590 --> 00:22:40,020
You jerk, how could you not recognize me?

385
00:22:40,020 --> 00:22:41,490
Hey, how could I not remember you?

386
00:22:41,490 --> 00:22:42,540
See? See?

387
00:22:42,540 --> 00:22:45,490
Gosh, how long has it been?

388
00:22:45,490 --> 00:22:47,900
Oh, you heard I was back.

389
00:22:47,900 --> 00:22:49,380
Not at all.

390
00:22:49,380 --> 00:22:50,880
We came to eat and here you were.

391
00:22:50,880 --> 00:22:52,950
Ma'am, three soft tofu stews, please!

392
00:22:52,950 --> 00:22:55,030
Aigoo, eat something more expensive.

393
00:22:55,030 --> 00:22:57,170
I spent my paycheck already.

394
00:22:57,170 --> 00:22:59,420
 Make three delicious soft tofu stews. 

395
00:22:59,420 --> 00:23:02,830
What's this? You didn't come to see me?

396
00:23:02,830 --> 00:23:05,090
I'm hungry. Let's talk after we eat.

397
00:23:05,090 --> 00:23:06,310
I'm starving.

398
00:23:06,310 --> 00:23:09,800
All right, eat up. I hope you get indigestion.

399
00:23:09,800 --> 00:23:13,090
- I'll sue you. 
 - Yes, and I'm an attorney.

400
00:23:14,970 --> 00:23:18,890
Your mom bragged a lot about you coming.

401
00:23:18,890 --> 00:23:20,680
  ­ 

402
00:23:20,680 --> 00:23:23,720
- Really? 
 - You'll drink with us tonight, right?

403
00:23:23,720 --> 00:23:26,500
Sorry. I've got some work to do today.

404
00:23:26,500 --> 00:23:28,300
Let's set a date and grab drinks another time.

405
00:23:28,300 --> 00:23:32,020
- You're out. 
 - Aigoo, thanks a lot.

406
00:23:33,590 --> 00:23:34,850
Yes, Jin Su?

407
00:23:34,850 --> 00:23:37,630
 Yes, Attorney Oh. We're heading down right now. 

408
00:23:37,630 --> 00:23:40,490
 We're almost there. We're starving. 

409
00:23:40,490 --> 00:23:42,630
But right now...

410
00:23:43,360 --> 00:23:45,950
I don't think you should come here right now.

411
00:23:45,950 --> 00:23:47,820
Why not?

412
00:23:47,820 --> 00:23:51,230
 There are quite a few townspeople here. 

413
00:23:51,230 --> 00:23:54,770
Wow, it sure is a famous restaurant. Do we have to wait in line?

414
00:23:54,770 --> 00:23:57,570
 No, it's not about it being a famous restaurant. 

415
00:23:57,570 --> 00:23:59,740
 There are many Greenview employees here. 

416
00:23:59,740 --> 00:24:04,110
 We can't have rumors spread about the company being sold. 

417
00:24:05,070 --> 00:24:08,380
 I'll go out to the main road right now. 

418
00:24:08,380 --> 00:24:09,910
Okay.

419
00:24:12,790 --> 00:24:15,860
Attorney Oh is coming out to the main road.

420
00:24:20,870 --> 00:24:22,940
Mom, I'm leaving.

421
00:24:22,940 --> 00:24:25,950
Where are you going? You should eat the tofu!

422
00:24:25,950 --> 00:24:28,070
- Leaving? 
 - I'm sorry,

423
00:24:28,070 --> 00:24:30,170
but something urgent came up at work.

424
00:24:30,170 --> 00:24:31,330
I need to go.

425
00:24:31,330 --> 00:24:33,720
Let's set a date to grab drinks soon.

426
00:24:33,720 --> 00:24:35,800
- Eat before you go. 
 - But the food came out.

427
00:24:35,800 --> 00:24:38,460
Sorry. It's an urgent matter. I'll call you.

428
00:24:38,460 --> 00:24:40,210
Okay, get back safely.

429
00:24:40,210 --> 00:24:43,300
Mom, I'm sorry.

430
00:24:44,170 --> 00:24:46,460
See you. See you!

431
00:25:14,500 --> 00:25:18,510
Turns out all my close friends work at Greenview.

432
00:25:18,510 --> 00:25:20,730
Since it's your hometown?

433
00:25:20,730 --> 00:25:25,200
Yes, it's not like there are any big companies around here.

434
00:25:25,200 --> 00:25:30,220
Then what happens to your friends when the golf course is sold?

435
00:25:30,220 --> 00:25:35,190
Since the buyer wants to run the golf course, they'll be carried over.

436
00:25:35,190 --> 00:25:38,640
Yes, though the CEO will change.

437
00:25:39,210 --> 00:25:41,240
Only the CEO?

438
00:25:41,240 --> 00:25:44,940
Because Greenview is doing well, there is a potential buyer.

439
00:25:44,940 --> 00:25:49,530
If the CEO is being fired for doing well, isn't that unfair?

440
00:25:49,530 --> 00:25:51,420
That's basically what's happening.

441
00:25:51,420 --> 00:25:54,400
Gosh, then I don't want to be a CEO.

442
00:25:54,400 --> 00:25:57,080
Whoa, I won't make you CEO either.

443
00:25:57,080 --> 00:26:00,290
I don't know what's good about being a CEO.

444
00:26:00,290 --> 00:26:04,900
Just looking at the executives, they're constantly worried about losing their jobs.

445
00:26:04,900 --> 00:26:06,620
They don't seem to be doing any work either.

446
00:26:06,620 --> 00:26:07,930
I suppose.

447
00:26:07,930 --> 00:26:12,000
That's why executives always engage in politics.

448
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:14,090
Yes...

449
00:26:14,090 --> 00:26:17,000
I think it's better to just be an employee.

450
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:20,880
But if you don't become an executive, you'll be fired before that.

451
00:26:26,390 --> 00:26:31,710
If we succeed in this sale, I'll become an executive.

452
00:26:34,130 --> 00:26:36,640
Congratulations, Mr. Yun.

453
00:26:36,640 --> 00:26:38,460
Yes, congratulations.

454
00:26:39,740 --> 00:26:46,270
♫  Congratulations  ♫

455
00:26:46,270 --> 00:26:49,600
♫  Congratulations  ♫

456
00:26:49,600 --> 00:26:56,410
♫  Congratulations on your promotion  ♫

457
00:27:14,710 --> 00:27:17,630
The CEO here will probably get mad, right?

458
00:27:17,630 --> 00:27:19,230
Jin Su.

459
00:27:19,230 --> 00:27:22,700
You won't get offended and curse at him again, right?

460
00:27:22,700 --> 00:27:25,420
Look at me. Let's practice.

461
00:27:26,160 --> 00:27:29,390
This time, I'll hold it in.

462
00:27:33,380 --> 00:27:36,480
Hello, you're Team Leader Yun Ju No, right?

463
00:27:36,480 --> 00:27:38,820
Hello, CEO Lee Hyeong Taek?

464
00:27:38,820 --> 00:27:40,350
I'm Yun Ju No.

465
00:27:40,350 --> 00:27:42,400
Nice to meet you.

466
00:27:42,400 --> 00:27:43,490
Let's head inside.

467
00:27:43,490 --> 00:27:46,790
Let's talk while having some tea inside.

468
00:27:55,000 --> 00:27:59,130
Strangely enough, the mood doesn't seem to be that bad.

469
00:27:59,130 --> 00:28:00,970
I know, right?

470
00:28:02,810 --> 00:28:05,190
Please come in.

471
00:28:06,630 --> 00:28:08,160
Please take a seat here.

472
00:28:08,160 --> 00:28:11,130
No, you should sit there, CEO.

473
00:28:11,130 --> 00:28:13,340
Aigoo. Aigoo, please take a seat.

474
00:28:13,340 --> 00:28:14,900
Oh, okay.

475
00:28:15,820 --> 00:28:17,940
Please, sit here.

476
00:28:21,000 --> 00:28:22,630
Aigoo...

477
00:28:24,040 --> 00:28:27,030
At first, when I saw the four of you here,

478
00:28:27,030 --> 00:28:28,820
I thought you came to take some swings.

479
00:28:28,820 --> 00:28:32,340
Oh, sorry. We're not customers.

480
00:28:32,340 --> 00:28:34,030
Aigoo, no, no.

481
00:28:34,030 --> 00:28:36,800
I don't mean I'm disappointed you weren't customers.

482
00:28:36,800 --> 00:28:38,600
Please, take a seat.

483
00:28:38,600 --> 00:28:40,030
Okay.

484
00:28:54,270 --> 00:28:57,090
I received the call from HQ.

485
00:28:57,090 --> 00:28:59,350
You'll be selling our CC?

486
00:28:59,350 --> 00:29:02,490
Yes. It's not confirmed yet.

487
00:29:02,490 --> 00:29:05,110
But Sanin is experiencing financial difficulties.

488
00:29:05,110 --> 00:29:09,030
We've no choice but to proactively sell subsidiaries.

489
00:29:09,030 --> 00:29:12,750
Yes, I understand.

490
00:29:15,100 --> 00:29:19,630
Then will the golf course be shut down?

491
00:29:19,630 --> 00:29:23,430
No, the potential buyer plans to run it.

492
00:29:23,430 --> 00:29:26,890
Thus, the employees will be carried over,

493
00:29:26,890 --> 00:29:32,250
but please keep the sale confidential until it's finalized.

494
00:29:32,250 --> 00:29:36,890
For employees, the news of the company being sold

495
00:29:36,890 --> 00:29:39,620
could cause some agitation.

496
00:29:39,620 --> 00:29:42,720
Yes... I suppose so.

497
00:29:42,720 --> 00:29:46,860
And if you need to let us know anything, you should tell us now.

498
00:29:46,860 --> 00:29:52,140
The buyer will conduct a thorough due diligence to assess its value.

499
00:29:52,140 --> 00:29:56,390
If issues are discovered, then it'd be difficult to resolve.

500
00:29:56,910 --> 00:30:01,280
Other than the business being slow, there's nothing like that.

501
00:30:02,270 --> 00:30:07,320
Isn't it still doing better than other golf courses?

502
00:30:07,320 --> 00:30:10,470
Well, we tried our best.

503
00:30:10,470 --> 00:30:11,870
But I'm glad...

504
00:30:11,870 --> 00:30:15,720
they'll continue to operate the golf course.

505
00:30:15,720 --> 00:30:18,500
I thought I was going to be fired.

506
00:30:21,410 --> 00:30:24,280
The potential buyer of Greenview CC

507
00:30:24,280 --> 00:30:27,830
asks for a change in CEO.

508
00:30:31,800 --> 00:30:35,820
Is it not possible for me to continue as the CEO?

509
00:30:35,820 --> 00:30:39,270
The buyer has made it a priority condition,

510
00:30:39,270 --> 00:30:41,200
so that'd be difficult.

511
00:30:41,200 --> 00:30:45,740
But we can move you to another Sanin subsidiary,

512
00:30:45,740 --> 00:30:49,750
or help you transition to another company.

513
00:30:53,280 --> 00:30:55,900
There's a chance the sale might not happen, right?

514
00:30:55,900 --> 00:30:58,840
Yes, that's also possible.

515
00:30:59,590 --> 00:31:04,380
Then could I take some time to think about

516
00:31:04,380 --> 00:31:07,230
what I should do in the future?

517
00:31:07,230 --> 00:31:11,620
I also need to discuss this with my wife.

518
00:31:11,620 --> 00:31:14,670
Yes, please take sufficient time to think

519
00:31:14,670 --> 00:31:18,180
and just let us know during the due diligence period.

520
00:31:18,180 --> 00:31:21,540
Then can I assume that

521
00:31:21,540 --> 00:31:24,900
you'll allow us to conduct due diligence?

522
00:31:25,880 --> 00:31:29,340
Well, I have no choice.

523
00:31:32,950 --> 00:31:34,950
Oh, hello.

524
00:31:37,030 --> 00:31:39,360
Hey, Manager Jeong.

525
00:31:44,940 --> 00:31:48,000
She is our Financial Manager.

526
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:50,210
She manages our resources.

527
00:31:50,210 --> 00:31:51,630
I also have to ask

528
00:31:51,630 --> 00:31:54,180
Ms. Jeong if there's something I don't know.

529
00:31:54,180 --> 00:31:56,350
No, that's not true.

530
00:32:00,700 --> 00:32:02,290
Do you two know each other?

531
00:32:02,290 --> 00:32:04,220
Oh, yes, well...

532
00:32:04,220 --> 00:32:06,190
we're childhood friends.

533
00:32:06,190 --> 00:32:08,810
Actually, I grew up in this neighborhood.

534
00:32:08,810 --> 00:32:12,770
Oh, I see.

535
00:32:17,970 --> 00:32:20,420
Well, have a safe trip back.

536
00:32:20,420 --> 00:32:23,190
Thank you. I'll await your call.

537
00:32:36,960 --> 00:32:39,530
They came from the HQ, right?

538
00:32:39,530 --> 00:32:44,440
Yes, they came to do a fact-finding survey.

539
00:32:46,280 --> 00:32:48,120
Let's head inside.

540
00:32:50,430 --> 00:32:53,500
I feel a bit sorry for the CEO.

541
00:32:53,500 --> 00:32:55,680
I understand how you feel, Jin Su,

542
00:32:55,680 --> 00:32:59,520
but it's better to be straightforward with the truth.

543
00:32:59,520 --> 00:33:01,260
Pardon?

544
00:33:07,430 --> 00:33:10,340
Though you said you felt sorry,

545
00:33:10,340 --> 00:33:13,930
what you actually feel is pity.

546
00:33:13,930 --> 00:33:16,470
Honestly, pity isn't

547
00:33:16,470 --> 00:33:18,790
what we should feel

548
00:33:18,790 --> 00:33:22,250
toward the chief executive of this place.

549
00:33:22,250 --> 00:33:25,960
It's better for him to know exactly what's happening

550
00:33:25,960 --> 00:33:27,600
to consider his next steps.

551
00:33:27,600 --> 00:33:32,100
That's true, but it seems unfair.

552
00:33:46,110 --> 00:33:48,220
 If CEO Lee Hyeong Taek was a good executive, 

553
00:33:48,220 --> 00:33:50,740
 he'll be evaluated as such. 

554
00:33:50,740 --> 00:33:55,100
 Though we don't know when or how that will happen. 

555
00:34:15,600 --> 00:34:20,170
Then he may never be properly evaluated, right?

556
00:34:20,170 --> 00:34:22,360
That's possible.

557
00:34:22,360 --> 00:34:23,630
What can he do, then?

558
00:34:23,630 --> 00:34:26,970
What would you do if you were in his shoes?

559
00:34:27,620 --> 00:34:29,550
I don't know.

560
00:34:29,550 --> 00:34:34,200
I think I would just keep carrying on as usual.

561
00:34:34,200 --> 00:34:35,560
You are doing that.

562
00:34:35,560 --> 00:34:37,310
Yes.

563
00:34:39,810 --> 00:34:41,580
  ­ 

564
00:34:48,170 --> 00:34:51,170
What brings you here, Director Jo?

565
00:34:51,170 --> 00:34:54,020
I have something to ask you briefly.

566
00:34:54,020 --> 00:34:56,130
Me?

567
00:34:56,930 --> 00:34:58,480
Yes.

568
00:34:58,480 --> 00:34:59,950
Since I'm in HR,

569
00:34:59,950 --> 00:35:03,840
I just need to focus on personnel matters.

570
00:35:03,840 --> 00:35:07,410
Maybe it's because the subsidiary CEOs have different perspectives.

571
00:35:07,410 --> 00:35:10,990
The company atmosphere feels too heated lately.

572
00:35:10,990 --> 00:35:13,630
Everyone's so sensitive.

573
00:35:13,630 --> 00:35:15,830
I see.

574
00:35:15,830 --> 00:35:19,690
The company is in a difficult financial state,

575
00:35:19,690 --> 00:35:21,800
so they must be quite worried.

576
00:35:21,800 --> 00:35:23,230
That's what I mean.

577
00:35:23,230 --> 00:35:24,760
We should help each other more

578
00:35:24,760 --> 00:35:27,960
if the company is struggling.

579
00:35:30,570 --> 00:35:33,640
I mean, well...

580
00:35:33,640 --> 00:35:36,710
I think Mr. Yun may have a rigid personality.

581
00:35:36,710 --> 00:35:40,690
But everything he says is correct.

582
00:35:40,690 --> 00:35:44,070
But it's hard to take Mr. Yun's side

583
00:35:44,070 --> 00:35:47,320
because I don't know whose head will roll.

584
00:35:49,830 --> 00:35:54,360
Well, Mr. Yun is also just doing his job.

585
00:35:54,360 --> 00:35:56,770
You know our company's situation isn't great.

586
00:35:56,770 --> 00:35:58,150
Of course.

587
00:35:58,150 --> 00:35:59,570
It's a situation

588
00:35:59,570 --> 00:36:02,400
where someone will have to suffer loss.

589
00:36:02,400 --> 00:36:05,090
Since I'm a HR administrator,

590
00:36:05,090 --> 00:36:08,490
I don't have anything to do with M&amp;A.

591
00:36:12,790 --> 00:36:15,490
Oh, of course.

592
00:36:15,490 --> 00:36:18,640
Our situation is...

593
00:36:18,640 --> 00:36:21,790
different from the subsidiary CEOs'.

594
00:36:23,890 --> 00:36:28,790
Though Mr. Yun seems to be a bit stubborn,

595
00:36:28,790 --> 00:36:32,300
he knows how to respect the hierarchy.

596
00:36:32,300 --> 00:36:33,730
Yes.

597
00:36:33,730 --> 00:36:35,420
If he joins the board of directors,

598
00:36:35,420 --> 00:36:38,510
he'll be flexible and do well.

599
00:36:38,510 --> 00:36:41,850
Yes, I think so, too.

600
00:36:42,810 --> 00:36:44,100
You should go home now.

601
00:36:44,100 --> 00:36:45,770
Yes, yes.

602
00:36:46,750 --> 00:36:47,920
Yes, Director.

603
00:36:47,920 --> 00:36:50,520
We want to proceed with the sale of the golf course.

604
00:36:50,520 --> 00:36:54,620
 Then should we sign the MOU first? 

605
00:36:54,620 --> 00:36:56,970
The buyer will also come, right?

606
00:36:56,970 --> 00:36:58,430
 Yes, of course. 

607
00:36:58,430 --> 00:37:01,980
 But he wants to meet at the golf course. 

608
00:37:04,690 --> 00:37:06,540
At Greenview?

609
00:37:06,540 --> 00:37:09,110
 Yes. He's a bit impatient. 

610
00:37:09,110 --> 00:37:11,880
 He wants to see the golf course in person. 

611
00:37:14,000 --> 00:37:15,860
Okay, let's do that.

612
00:37:15,860 --> 00:37:18,190
I'll see you there.

613
00:37:26,950 --> 00:37:28,560
Did you wait long?

614
00:37:28,560 --> 00:37:30,410
No, sir.

615
00:37:34,600 --> 00:37:36,550
We'll sign an MOU for Greenview tomorrow

616
00:37:36,550 --> 00:37:39,700
and start the due diligence.

617
00:37:39,700 --> 00:37:43,810
It's a relief that a buyer appeared quickly.

618
00:37:43,810 --> 00:37:45,110
Yes.

619
00:37:46,000 --> 00:37:48,340
You can just handle the matter.

620
00:37:48,340 --> 00:37:51,080
What else is there for us to talk about?

621
00:37:51,080 --> 00:37:52,700
When this deal is done,

622
00:37:52,700 --> 00:37:55,320
I'll join the board of directors.

623
00:37:55,320 --> 00:37:57,730
I was curious what the current executives

624
00:37:57,730 --> 00:37:59,800
would think.

625
00:37:59,800 --> 00:38:02,520
Are you worried they'll put you through a hazing?

626
00:38:04,260 --> 00:38:06,720
The work that you're doing right now

627
00:38:06,720 --> 00:38:10,470
is cutting out Sanin's wounds.

628
00:38:10,470 --> 00:38:15,190
Since the chairman essentially approved of your work,

629
00:38:15,190 --> 00:38:18,660
this is a big deal among executives.

630
00:38:19,550 --> 00:38:21,040
But it doesn't look like

631
00:38:21,040 --> 00:38:24,860
the situation is disadvantageous for you.

632
00:38:25,630 --> 00:38:29,770
You just keep doing what you've been doing.

633
00:38:29,770 --> 00:38:31,390
Okay.

634
00:38:46,900 --> 00:38:48,130
Hey, Director Jo.

635
00:38:48,130 --> 00:38:49,840
Hello.

636
00:39:24,330 --> 00:39:28,820
Wow, Mr. Jo, you've improved a lot.

637
00:39:29,620 --> 00:39:32,170
But you're good, too, Mr. Ha.

638
00:39:32,170 --> 00:39:35,500
I just swing once in a while to work out.

639
00:39:35,500 --> 00:39:37,280
But I've got some business coming up,

640
00:39:37,280 --> 00:39:38,800
so I wanted to practice.

641
00:39:38,800 --> 00:39:40,020
I see.

642
00:39:40,020 --> 00:39:43,300
If you want to do business, you need to play golf.

643
00:39:44,100 --> 00:39:46,360
You should come out to the field sometime.

644
00:39:46,360 --> 00:39:48,890
Oh, okay.

645
00:39:52,800 --> 00:39:54,410
Come on now.

646
00:39:54,410 --> 00:39:57,060
Your shoulders are tight today.

647
00:39:57,060 --> 00:39:59,340
Oh, yes.

648
00:39:59,340 --> 00:40:02,480
What's up? Is something complicated going on?

649
00:40:02,780 --> 00:40:06,070
Me? No, not really.

650
00:40:08,340 --> 00:40:13,310
In golf, hitting farther doesn't mean you win.

651
00:40:13,310 --> 00:40:15,870
You need to set the right direction.

652
00:40:15,870 --> 00:40:18,630
If you keep the direction consistent,

653
00:40:18,630 --> 00:40:20,750
you'll win.

654
00:40:20,750 --> 00:40:22,320
I see.

655
00:40:23,960 --> 00:40:27,110
I hope you'll be like that, Mr. Jo.

656
00:40:30,210 --> 00:40:32,110
Well...

657
00:40:32,110 --> 00:40:34,180
Mr. Ha, honestly...

658
00:40:34,180 --> 00:40:36,700
Yes, honestly?

659
00:40:36,700 --> 00:40:41,790
How about you get along better with Mr. Yun?

660
00:40:41,790 --> 00:40:42,730
What?

661
00:40:42,730 --> 00:40:47,510
I just thought maybe you could treat him a bit nicer.

662
00:40:47,510 --> 00:40:49,900
You'll be seeing him often from now on.

663
00:40:52,110 --> 00:40:54,900
So that's the direction you've chosen, huh?

664
00:40:54,900 --> 00:40:57,990
Aigoo, it's not that I've chosen that direction.

665
00:40:57,990 --> 00:41:02,110
Honestly, our company doesn't just follow the board's opinion

666
00:41:02,110 --> 00:41:04,270
nor do we hold a lot of shares.

667
00:41:04,270 --> 00:41:07,350
If the chairman says okay, that's how we roll.

668
00:41:07,350 --> 00:41:09,330
Okay.

669
00:41:12,350 --> 00:41:16,510
I didn't realize you were such a romantic, Mr. Jo.

670
00:41:16,510 --> 00:41:17,920
Pardon?

671
00:41:21,340 --> 00:41:22,850
I mean...

672
00:41:31,100 --> 00:41:33,190
Get home safely.

673
00:41:38,190 --> 00:41:41,070
Romantic? Romantic?

674
00:41:52,330 --> 00:41:54,600
Hey, CEO Kim. Are you outside?

675
00:41:54,600 --> 00:41:57,070
 I'm out to have dinner with my family. 

676
00:41:57,070 --> 00:41:59,120
Aigoo, I'm interrupting your family meal.

677
00:41:59,120 --> 00:42:01,540
Oh, no, it's okay.

678
00:42:03,720 --> 00:42:06,040
 I just had something to tell you. 

679
00:42:06,040 --> 00:42:07,570
 Do you have some time later? 

680
00:42:07,570 --> 00:42:08,960
Yes, I do.

681
00:42:08,960 --> 00:42:12,670
 Well, then... 

682
00:42:12,670 --> 00:42:14,890
 Let's meet at the Japanese place we go to often. 

683
00:42:14,890 --> 00:42:17,180
 I'll make a reservation and give you a call. 

684
00:42:17,180 --> 00:42:19,600
 Enjoy your dinner with your family. 

685
00:42:19,600 --> 00:42:22,300
Okay, okay. Let's do that, yes.

686
00:42:29,190 --> 00:42:30,890
I'm sorry to cut you off while you were talking.

687
00:42:30,890 --> 00:42:33,540
I got a call from my family.

688
00:42:34,390 --> 00:42:35,780
Well,

689
00:42:37,830 --> 00:42:40,420
where was I again?

690
00:42:41,150 --> 00:42:43,140
You were saying the game of Go...

691
00:42:43,140 --> 00:42:44,680
That it's fun.

692
00:42:44,680 --> 00:42:46,700
That I should learn.

693
00:42:48,240 --> 00:42:51,790
That was just a meaningless chat.

694
00:42:52,670 --> 00:42:55,350
What I really wanted to say was...

695
00:42:55,350 --> 00:42:59,490
- Yes? 
 - You know how we're preparing to enter into e-commerce?

696
00:42:59,520 --> 00:43:01,100
Yes.

697
00:43:01,860 --> 00:43:06,440
We don't plan to hire external personnel for it.

698
00:43:06,440 --> 00:43:10,730
And I know how well you've run Sanin Mart.

699
00:43:10,730 --> 00:43:12,190
Yes,

700
00:43:12,190 --> 00:43:15,720
I should assist you in handling e-commerce well.

701
00:43:15,720 --> 00:43:17,830
No.

702
00:43:17,830 --> 00:43:20,140
I'm going to retire.

703
00:43:20,680 --> 00:43:23,900
B-But... w-why?

704
00:43:23,900 --> 00:43:28,640
Is that why Mr. Yun is becoming an executive?

705
00:43:29,400 --> 00:43:34,830
No, what I'm saying is that you should do it.

706
00:43:34,830 --> 00:43:37,850
What do you mean? You should do it, Mr. Lee.

707
00:43:37,850 --> 00:43:41,120
I should retire now. I'm getting up there.

708
00:43:42,200 --> 00:43:44,930
Then wh-what about Mr. Yun?

709
00:43:44,930 --> 00:43:49,990
Mr. Yun also doesn't plan to stay here forever.

710
00:43:53,390 --> 00:43:58,320
So transitioning to e-commerce

711
00:43:58,320 --> 00:44:01,230
will become an opportunity for you.

712
00:44:05,540 --> 00:44:08,380
I didn't realize that was your intent.

713
00:44:08,380 --> 00:44:10,290
Honestly,

714
00:44:10,290 --> 00:44:15,390
I felt a bit hurt.

715
00:44:15,390 --> 00:44:18,130
I didn't know your bigger picture in mind...

716
00:44:19,600 --> 00:44:22,440
Then can I assume that...

717
00:44:23,070 --> 00:44:25,820
you're okay with e-commerce?

718
00:44:25,820 --> 00:44:27,560
Of course.

719
00:44:27,560 --> 00:44:30,360
E-commerce is ultimately distribution, after all.

720
00:44:30,360 --> 00:44:32,350
- It is distribution. 
 - Oh, yes.

721
00:44:32,350 --> 00:44:34,700
Please pour me a glass, too.

722
00:44:39,820 --> 00:44:42,120
   

723
00:44:44,770 --> 00:44:46,830
You can take the call.

724
00:44:46,830 --> 00:44:50,320
No, it's just my wife telling me to buy something.

725
00:44:56,000 --> 00:44:58,600
- Hey, stop the car. 
 - Okay.

726
00:45:08,110 --> 00:45:10,990
These jerks are scheming.

727
00:45:18,060 --> 00:45:20,070
Yes, CEO Lee.

728
00:45:20,070 --> 00:45:22,860
I don't think the numbers will line up tomorrow.

729
00:45:22,860 --> 00:45:26,820
Yes. You'll have to bring one more person.

730
00:45:26,820 --> 00:45:28,910
Yes, okay.

731
00:45:29,890 --> 00:45:32,310
Yes, Mr. Choi. We've arrived.

732
00:45:32,310 --> 00:45:34,730
 Oh, yes, Mr. Yun. 

733
00:45:34,730 --> 00:45:36,770
 We've been here for a while already. 

734
00:45:36,770 --> 00:45:39,030
 We're out on the course. 

735
00:45:41,090 --> 00:45:44,070
Then I'll wait for you in the lobby.

736
00:45:44,070 --> 00:45:45,910
 I think it'll take a while. 

737
00:45:45,910 --> 00:45:47,160
 Do you want to come over? 

738
00:45:47,160 --> 00:45:48,980
 I'll send a caddie for you. 

739
00:45:53,940 --> 00:45:56,280
Then let's do the paperwork next time.

740
00:45:56,280 --> 00:45:58,620
 No, our CEO also feels bad 

741
00:45:58,620 --> 00:46:01,790
 and he wants to meet you and sign today. 

742
00:46:06,510 --> 00:46:08,630
Isn't this too much?

743
00:46:08,630 --> 00:46:09,980
Yes.

744
00:46:09,980 --> 00:46:13,710
Even if the buyer has the upper hand,

745
00:46:13,710 --> 00:46:15,730
this is too much.

746
00:46:19,780 --> 00:46:21,370
Let's go.

747
00:46:42,410 --> 00:46:44,520
 The road curves up ahead. 

748
00:46:44,520 --> 00:46:47,150
 Please hold onto the safety bar. 

749
00:46:57,430 --> 00:46:59,380
 Good shot! 

750
00:47:05,860 --> 00:47:08,210
I'm sorry to have you come all the way here.

751
00:47:08,210 --> 00:47:09,790
Let's go.

752
00:47:11,600 --> 00:47:14,010
We can't interrupt his tee shot.

753
00:47:17,250 --> 00:47:19,530
 - Nice!  
 - Let's go.

754
00:47:25,830 --> 00:47:30,250
Aigoo, it's been a while, Mr. Yun.

755
00:47:31,740 --> 00:47:35,030
- Yes. 
 - You've met already, right?

756
00:47:37,530 --> 00:47:38,840
You didn't know?

757
00:47:38,840 --> 00:47:40,940
I'll buy this place.

758
00:47:41,830 --> 00:47:43,500
I see.

759
00:47:43,500 --> 00:47:45,470
We're in your care.

760
00:47:45,470 --> 00:47:47,450
No, I should be saying that.

761
00:47:47,450 --> 00:47:49,780
Let me buy this place for cheap.

762
00:47:51,790 --> 00:47:53,840
How about we stop playing golf now?

763
00:47:53,840 --> 00:47:55,170
Whoa, whoa, no!

764
00:47:55,170 --> 00:47:57,590
I'm winning right now!

765
00:47:59,260 --> 00:48:03,170
Hyeongnim, Mr. Yun will cry if you keep this up!

766
00:48:05,210 --> 00:48:07,400
Don't take this the wrong way.

767
00:48:07,400 --> 00:48:09,920
CEO Lee and I are really close,

768
00:48:09,920 --> 00:48:11,990
so we've met occasionally, even after he left

769
00:48:11,990 --> 00:48:14,010
and played golf together, too.

770
00:48:14,010 --> 00:48:17,160
But he said there was a golf course he wanted to buy

771
00:48:17,160 --> 00:48:19,080
and asked me to come with him

772
00:48:19,080 --> 00:48:21,210
to see if it's all right.

773
00:48:22,360 --> 00:48:26,120
I'm sure you knew we were trying to sell the golf course.

774
00:48:26,120 --> 00:48:28,980
That's why I told you not to take it the wrong way.

775
00:48:28,980 --> 00:48:31,680
I only found out after I arrived, too!

776
00:48:33,030 --> 00:48:34,970
There comes CEO Lee now.

777
00:48:35,860 --> 00:48:38,090
He's got a straightforward personality,

778
00:48:38,090 --> 00:48:40,320
which is better for deals.

779
00:48:40,320 --> 00:48:41,980
If he doesn't listen to you, just tell me.

780
00:48:41,980 --> 00:48:44,760
He'll listen to anything I say.

781
00:48:47,790 --> 00:48:50,870
Then you two should talk. I'll get going.

782
00:48:50,870 --> 00:48:53,130
Leaving? No drinks?

783
00:48:53,130 --> 00:48:54,900
Come on, CEO Lee.

784
00:48:54,900 --> 00:48:57,790
If we drink after exercising, it's all for nothing.

785
00:48:57,790 --> 00:48:59,870
We shouldn't have started at all.

786
00:49:00,760 --> 00:49:02,210
Right?

787
00:49:03,720 --> 00:49:07,080
♫  Welcome to your new life ♫

788
00:49:08,060 --> 00:49:09,800
Mr. Yun,

789
00:49:09,800 --> 00:49:11,920
it's not easy to become an executive.

790
00:49:11,920 --> 00:49:13,100
Got it?

791
00:49:13,930 --> 00:49:17,830
♫  Welcome to your new life ♫

792
00:49:18,840 --> 00:49:20,680
Bye now.

793
00:49:26,040 --> 00:49:27,770
Wow...

794
00:49:27,770 --> 00:49:31,810
My body feels light after exercising.

795
00:49:31,810 --> 00:49:34,120
It feels light.

796
00:49:41,700 --> 00:49:46,590
CEO, is there a reason you asked to deal on a no-name basis?

797
00:49:46,590 --> 00:49:48,440
Yes.

798
00:49:48,440 --> 00:49:51,300
If such info is leaked, I was afraid

799
00:49:51,300 --> 00:49:53,940
someone may manipulate the stock prices.

800
00:49:57,560 --> 00:50:00,620
Yes, I suppose that's possible.

801
00:50:00,620 --> 00:50:03,160
You're certain you want to acquire it?

802
00:50:03,160 --> 00:50:05,460
I'm certain.

803
00:50:06,390 --> 00:50:07,960
Aren't we signing today?

804
00:50:07,960 --> 00:50:09,990
Yes, that's right.

805
00:50:26,760 --> 00:50:28,940
I'll give it back after reviewing it.

806
00:50:33,530 --> 00:50:35,750
Are you still an intern?

807
00:50:37,610 --> 00:50:39,240
Yes.

808
00:50:41,940 --> 00:50:44,090
This is it, right?

