924
00:57:22,270 --> 00:57:25,420
Yes, probably?

925
00:57:40,420 --> 00:57:43,780
I'm planning to quit.

926
00:57:45,710 --> 00:57:49,270
Should I find another position at another subsidiary?

927
00:57:50,710 --> 00:57:52,300
No.

928
00:57:53,020 --> 00:57:55,930
Sanin's not in a great situation right now.

929
00:57:55,930 --> 00:57:58,110
If I go to another subsidiary,

930
00:57:58,110 --> 00:58:01,620
I might be taking away someone else's spot.

931
00:58:01,620 --> 00:58:04,650
I think it's best for me to just step away.

932
00:58:05,590 --> 00:58:08,060
Or we could help you transition to

933
00:58:08,060 --> 00:58:10,230
one of our partner companies.

934
00:58:13,390 --> 00:58:15,060
No,

935
00:58:15,060 --> 00:58:17,780
I'd like to take a break.

936
00:58:19,920 --> 00:58:23,080
Is there a reason?

937
00:58:24,580 --> 00:58:28,770
Actually, I'm a "Goose Dad."*
  (*Father living in Korea whilst family is abroad) 

938
00:58:29,820 --> 00:58:33,400
My wife and son are in the U.S.

939
00:58:35,070 --> 00:58:38,470
I want to live with them now.

940
00:58:46,310 --> 00:58:49,320
This is my son and his mother.

941
00:58:51,400 --> 00:58:55,430
I guess your wife works with flowers.

942
00:58:56,600 --> 00:58:58,120
Yes.

943
00:59:00,370 --> 00:59:03,260
Our son got into NYU,

944
00:59:03,260 --> 00:59:06,490
but the tuition is insane.

945
